The paper is concerned with Interactive Machine Learning, which involves creating systems that operate in environments alongside humans to achieve a task. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of reinforcement learning and robotic arms, which are common topics in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The paper also evaluates the method experimentally in a simulated environment for a grasping task using a robotic arm with variable grip settings, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories.
